1
00:01:39,479 --> 00:01:43,220
[Road to Success]

2
00:01:44,590 --> 00:01:47,930
[Episode 30]

3
00:01:51,150 --> 00:01:51,950
Later,

4
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:54,000
use this nail to pin the eel down.

5
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,200
I'll handle the rest.

6
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,280
This is...

7
00:01:56,310 --> 00:01:57,400
your...

8
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,640
s-signature dish?

9
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,430
Yeah,

10
00:01:59,430 --> 00:02:00,480
braised eel.

11
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,310
Let me tell you,

12
00:02:01,310 --> 00:02:04,480
my wife and Wang Tian both love it.

13
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:06,480
W-Wang Tian loves eel?

14
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,130
You're not afraid of eels, are you?

15
00:02:09,750 --> 00:02:10,280
I'm telling you,

16
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:12,000
Wang Tian hates cowardly men the most.

17
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,000
I-I'm not!

18
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,120
I never said I was afraid.

19
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,030
I can do it.

20
00:02:19,070 --> 00:02:19,720
Hold it.

21
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:21,490
Remember, nail the head.

22
00:02:21,490 --> 00:02:23,290
Be careful not to nail your hand.

23
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,120
Auntie!

24
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,030
You're back!

25
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:48,910
Yu Bo, you came.

26
00:02:50,030 --> 00:02:52,240
Why are you covered in so much mud?

27
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:54,560
My mom insisted on
checking out the construction site.

28
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,030
You're a civil engineering professor,

29
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:57,030
not a contractor.

30
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:58,450
Look at the mess on your clothes.

31
00:02:58,450 --> 00:03:00,370
A student of mine wanted me to
take a look at their project.

32
00:03:00,370 --> 00:03:01,400
Of course, I had to go, right?

33
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,040
Yeah.

34
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,030
Wang Tian, let me tell you...

35
00:03:04,030 --> 00:03:04,840
Well...

36
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:10,630
What's wrong?

37
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:11,490
Why are you gagging?

38
00:03:11,490 --> 00:03:12,620
Am I making you sick?

39
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:14,560
No, I...

40
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,440
It's just a reflex.

41
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:18,280
A reflex?

42
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,030
Excuse me.

43
00:03:20,030 --> 00:03:20,680
You guys clean up first.

44
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,560
I n-need to go to the bathroom.

45
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,790
Is he okay?

46
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:24,880
Mom,

47
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,840
are you okay?

48
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:30,040
-Hello, Professor Kang.
-And this is?

49
00:03:30,490 --> 00:03:32,400
This is Ms. Lin Wanxing,

50
00:03:32,430 --> 00:03:33,480
a fellow teacher

51
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,910
and my girlfriend.

52
00:03:36,220 --> 00:03:37,960
Hello, Ms. Lin.

53
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:38,960
Nice to meet you.

54
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,400
Kang Qiao.

55
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,560
You're back.

56
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:44,400
W-What happened?

57
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:49,680
Nothing. I'm just happy to be home.

58
00:03:50,790 --> 00:03:51,430
Ms. Lin,

59
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:52,870
I-I'll go wash up.

60
00:03:52,870 --> 00:03:54,280
I'm a mess.

61
00:03:54,910 --> 00:03:56,370
You guys keep her company.

62
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,430
You invited Ms. Lin over

63
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:00,840
without telling Mom beforehand?

64
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,520
And Ms. Lin just happened to catch
Mom looking so disheveled.

65
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,560
Wang,

66
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,840
you're dead.

67
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:10,680
Wait.

68
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,560
I made eel.

69
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,000
And braised!

70
00:04:15,590 --> 00:04:17,120
Let's all raise a glass to welcome

71
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:17,800
Ms. Lin Wanxing.

72
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:18,160
Thank you.

73
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:18,779
Welcome, welcome.

74
00:04:18,779 --> 00:04:19,790
Welcome, welcome.

75
00:04:19,790 --> 00:04:21,240
Welcome, welcome.

76
00:04:24,870 --> 00:04:25,500
Oh, right.

77
00:04:26,190 --> 00:04:27,720
This is your favorite,

78
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:29,000
braised eel.

79
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,110
If you don't like it,

80
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:32,950
let's switch to another dish.

81
00:04:32,950 --> 00:04:33,390
Let's switch to another dish.

82
00:04:33,390 --> 00:04:34,190
This is the one you love.

83
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:34,790
Thank you.

84
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,460
This one...

85
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,500
Let me do it. Let me.

86
00:04:55,030 --> 00:04:56,070
How about this?

87
00:04:56,070 --> 00:04:56,950
Well,

88
00:04:56,950 --> 00:04:58,560
tomorrow I'll come back and make you

89
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,000
braised soft-shell turtle—

90
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,910
freshly slaughtered.

91
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:01,660
Yu.

92
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:02,440
Yu can do it.

93
00:05:02,470 --> 00:05:03,120
He has great knife skills.

94
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,430
No, no, r-really, I can't.

95
00:05:04,430 --> 00:05:05,600
My knife skills aren't good.

96
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:06,390
Not good at all.

97
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:09,430
This is Wanxing's first time
visiting our home.

98
00:05:09,430 --> 00:05:11,120
Why didn't you tell me beforehand?

99
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,390
Why keep it from me?

100
00:05:13,070 --> 00:05:13,680
Well...

101
00:05:14,310 --> 00:05:15,110
It's just that

102
00:05:15,270 --> 00:05:18,120
you've been so busy lately with research,

103
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,160
writing papers,

104
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,840
and running around to construction sites.

105
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,030
I didn't want you to wear yourself out.

106
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:22,830
So,

107
00:05:22,860 --> 00:05:23,600
whatever I could handle myself,

108
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,560
I just went ahead a-and did it.

109
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:28,830
This whole table of dishes—

110
00:05:28,830 --> 00:05:30,390
it must have taken you all afternoon.

111
00:05:30,390 --> 00:05:31,790
Just about 4 or 5 hours.

112
00:05:31,810 --> 00:05:32,659
It was fine.

113
00:05:32,820 --> 00:05:33,650
Mom,

114
00:05:33,670 --> 00:05:35,470
for all the hard work
Dad put into this meal,

115
00:05:35,470 --> 00:05:36,730
forgive him this time.

116
00:05:37,909 --> 00:05:38,590
Dad,

117
00:05:38,610 --> 00:05:39,680
punish yourself with a drink,

118
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,280
and this matter will be over.

119
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,510
That's my boy.

120
00:05:45,170 --> 00:05:46,020
Your Majesty,

121
00:05:46,510 --> 00:05:47,750
I was wrong.

122
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:51,390
Blessings to the Empress Dowager.

123
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:52,270
At ease.

124
00:05:55,110 --> 00:05:55,870
Wanxing,

125
00:05:55,890 --> 00:05:56,720
try this dish.

126
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:58,540
It's my husband's specialty.

127
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,409
Give it a try.

128
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:02,120
This is my signature dish, braised eel.

129
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:02,870
It's a secret recipe.

130
00:06:02,870 --> 00:06:04,600
You can't get it anywhere else.

131
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:05,830
Come on, try it.

132
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:07,910
My wife and Tian both love it the most.

133
00:06:07,940 --> 00:06:09,510
Ms. Lin, I want some.

134
00:06:10,910 --> 00:06:13,040
You just can't help yourself, can you?

135
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,920
These noodles look great.

136
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,560
Let me try the broth first.

137
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,240
The broth is
what makes the noodles, right?

138
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:23,190
This is also Chairman Wang's specialty.

139
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:23,800
Dad,

140
00:06:23,830 --> 00:06:26,160
the broth is made from eel bones, right?

141
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:26,600
Right.

142
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,400
You just love the flavor, right?

143
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,360
Uncle and Auntie,

144
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:33,040
let me propose a toast.

145
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,460
I need to use the restroom.

146
00:06:39,430 --> 00:06:41,000
What a lightweight.

147
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:42,600
Wanxing,

148
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,000
a toast to you.

149
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,040
What are you doing?

150
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:47,040
Making her drink on her first visit?

151
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,130
I'll finish mine, and you do as you like.

152
00:06:49,130 --> 00:06:50,430
-Okay?
-You're putting her on the spot.

153
00:06:50,430 --> 00:06:51,600
If she doesn't drink,
it's disrespectful to you, right?

154
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,400
That's not it.

155
00:06:53,390 --> 00:06:54,770
In this house,

156
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,580
whether you respect me or not
doesn't matter.

157
00:06:56,580 --> 00:06:58,450
But you must respect
the lady of the house,

158
00:06:58,450 --> 00:06:59,070
right?

159
00:06:59,070 --> 00:07:01,000
Blessings to the Empress Dowager.

160
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,290
Come on, come on.

161
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,350
Right,

162
00:07:04,380 --> 00:07:05,190
Wanxing,

163
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:07,030
do you know

164
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:09,080
why I felt an instant connection with you?

165
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:10,080
That's because

166
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:12,490
you're very much like our Professor Kang.

167
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:17,270
I didn't study hard when I was a kid,

168
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,360
so I'm not very educated.

169
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:20,560
One year, when I was doing business
in Shenzhen,

170
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,830
I had a client whose surname was Situ.

171
00:07:22,830 --> 00:07:23,720
I even

172
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:25,240
tried to act clever and asked him,

173
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:25,920
"Sir,

174
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:28,160
is it that your father's surname is Si

175
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:30,020
and your mother's surname is Tu?"

176
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,830
That was so embarrassing.

177
00:07:31,830 --> 00:07:33,240
Things like that happened a lot.

178
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:33,800
So

179
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,360
I've always believed

180
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,040
that every family

181
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:38,730
needs an intelligent, well-educated woman—

182
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:40,170
that's what makes a household prosper.

183
00:07:40,170 --> 00:07:41,170
Remember that.

184
00:07:41,190 --> 00:07:44,240
Back then, I basically wore
Professor Kang down with my persistence

185
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,900
until she agreed to be with me.

186
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:50,700
I heard you were once the top scorer
on the college entrance exam, right?

187
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:51,830
What was your score?

188
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:53,680
Seven hundred and six points.

189
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,159
See? See?

190
00:07:55,630 --> 00:07:57,390
Compared to our Professor Kang,

191
00:07:57,390 --> 00:07:58,800
you're no couch.

192
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,510
"No slouch."

193
00:08:00,510 --> 00:08:03,480
Right, it's "no slouch." No slouch.

194
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:05,560
Anyway,

195
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,830
thank you so much

196
00:08:09,510 --> 00:08:11,630
for choosing our Wang Fa.

197
00:08:13,630 --> 00:08:15,040
To be honest, I also think

198
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:17,100
you two are a perfect match.

199
00:08:17,130 --> 00:08:18,210
He's not like

200
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,870
those delusional guys out there who are

201
00:08:19,870 --> 00:08:21,070
always chasing someone
way out of their league.

202
00:08:21,070 --> 00:08:22,020
Right, daughter?

203
00:08:22,020 --> 00:08:22,820
Dad.

204
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,390
Come on, eat up.

205
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:26,680
Let's have a drink together.

206
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,240
Come on, come on.

207
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,600
Cheers, cheers.

208
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,120
Cheers.

209
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,130
Welcome, Wanxing.

210
00:08:30,130 --> 00:08:31,040
Welcome, Wanxing.

211
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,720
Welcome, welcome.

212
00:08:33,659 --> 00:08:34,860
Don't drink too much.

213
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:35,840
I'm just happy.

214
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,549
Just a little bit.

215
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:37,909
Just a little.

216
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:39,909
Then eat more.

217
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,910
That's amazing.

218
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:57,270
Don't let me have all the fun.

219
00:08:57,270 --> 00:08:58,030
You young people,

220
00:08:58,030 --> 00:08:58,720
be more lively.

221
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,720
Don't just sit there with your phones.

222
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,550
Come here. Come on.

223
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:01,840
-Okay, I'll play.
-Go.

224
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:03,150
Let me play with you.

225
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,720
Why do you have to be part of everything?

226
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,880
I'm actually pretty good at this.

227
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:07,690
Really.

228
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:09,570
Is that so?

229
00:09:11,030 --> 00:09:12,600
I may be getting on in years,

230
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,130
but I still have
a strong competitive streak.

231
00:09:25,910 --> 00:09:27,480
See? I knew you were no good.

232
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,680
And you just had to...

233
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:30,490
Wanxing,

234
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,390
Wang Fa, come here.

235
00:09:31,390 --> 00:09:32,000
Wanxing, if you don't know how,

236
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:32,720
let Wang Fa teach you.

237
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:33,510
Come on, come on.

238
00:09:33,510 --> 00:09:35,120
She has zero athletic talent.

239
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:35,910
I'll do it.

240
00:09:36,270 --> 00:09:38,240
Let me play some rounds with our chairman.

241
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,380
Let Wanxing play.

242
00:09:39,410 --> 00:09:42,030
-Dad is on a completely different level.
-Let me get familiar with it first.

243
00:09:42,030 --> 00:09:44,540
He used to spear fish
on the production team back in the day.

244
00:09:44,540 --> 00:09:46,420
Come here and let the kids play.

245
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,930
Well, some things are better left unsaid.

246
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,030
Let me give it a try.

247
00:09:52,790 --> 00:09:53,360
How about

248
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:54,240
we have a round?

249
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,400
Sure.

250
00:09:57,620 --> 00:09:58,340
Okay.

251
00:09:58,390 --> 00:09:59,720
I think that's fine.

252
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:01,270
He sucks at darts.

253
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:02,240
Anyway, if you lose,

254
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,040
you have to do whatever she says.

255
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:07,600
I'll give you a head start.

256
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,480
You go first.

257
00:10:10,670 --> 00:10:11,790
This is going to be good.

258
00:10:11,790 --> 00:10:13,720
Challenge accepted.

259
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:20,390
-Clearly didn't inherit my genes.
-You really suck,

260
00:10:20,390 --> 00:10:21,320
little brother.

261
00:10:25,510 --> 00:10:27,600
Step aside.

262
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,000
Come on, Wanxing!

263
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:36,480
Not bad.

264
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:38,860
See? I knew Wanxing was good.

265
00:10:39,050 --> 00:10:40,120
Okay, you lost.

266
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,510
What do you want him to do?

267
00:10:41,510 --> 00:10:42,720
I have a suggestion.

268
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:45,120
Have you seen the photos of him
in women's clothes?

269
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,000
The one

270
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,960
where he's wearing a qipao
with a flower crown?

271
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,000
I just saw the photo upstairs.

272
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,260
Isn't that hilarious?

273
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:51,200
Okay.

274
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:53,290
How about a qipao and flower crown?

275
00:10:53,510 --> 00:10:54,720
Are you asking for it?

276
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,320
I think that's a great idea.

277
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:57,240
Duly noted.

278
00:10:58,910 --> 00:10:59,960
That's so fun, honey.

279
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:00,510
Come on, come on,

280
00:11:00,510 --> 00:11:01,000
honey,

281
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,930
how about I take you along
to try the flower crown too?

282
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,120
Come on, we're already here.

283
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:14,320
Just play one round.

284
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:15,120
No.

285
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:16,230
I'm very busy.

286
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:17,720
We have a guest,

287
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:20,600
and you're just sitting here
glued to your phone.

288
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:23,840
Fine.

289
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:24,870
If I win,

290
00:11:24,870 --> 00:11:27,080
you're not allowed to hang around
my office for no reason anymore.

291
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,550
And if I win,

292
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:30,240
you have to agree to one request of mine.

293
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,120
Deal.

294
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:34,500
Give the darts to them.

295
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,240
You got this.

296
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,650
Yu Bo used to compete in

297
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,600
professional dart tournaments
back in the UK.

298
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:45,120
No wonder he's so confident.

299
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:48,870
Nice!

300
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:51,130
As expected of Kang Qiao's daughter.

301
00:11:51,130 --> 00:11:52,210
So amazing.

302
00:12:06,150 --> 00:12:06,600
Wait.

303
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,030
Seriously?

304
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,080
When Wanxing hit the board,

305
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:10,840
you applauded so enthusiastically.

306
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:13,000
How come it's so cold when it's my turn?

307
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:18,240
Alright, go ahead.

308
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,440
What's your request?

309
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,630
My request is that...

310
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,910
you really look at me.

311
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,440
Look me in the eye, properly.

312
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:39,510
I just did.

313
00:12:41,090 --> 00:12:44,750
You're even more ordinary
than this quarter's financial report.

314
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,600
My sister's a master roaster.

315
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:52,000
How am I a master roaster?

316
00:12:52,390 --> 00:12:53,360
Your words are savage,

317
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,320
and your actions are even worse.

318
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:57,550
-Let's all play. Let me show you.
-You started that flower crown thing.

319
00:12:57,550 --> 00:12:59,000
I still haven't settled that score
with you.

320
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,000
You were smiling so happily in that photo

321
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,330
from when you were a kid.

322
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:02,840
I'll stick this dart in you.

323
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,360
D-Don't...

324
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:03,720
Dad,

325
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:04,380
look at him.

326
00:13:04,670 --> 00:13:06,330
Let Dad show you how it's done.

327
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,530
You can't lose to someone like him.

328
00:13:08,670 --> 00:13:09,360
Watch carefully.

329
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:10,510
It's too rowdy in here.

330
00:13:10,510 --> 00:13:11,600
Want to go out for some fresh air?

331
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:12,200
Standard posture.

332
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,200
Watch carefully.

333
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:18,120
-Dad, you're so good.
-Well, the old fox still has his tricks.

334
00:13:21,630 --> 00:13:23,000
Please excuse

335
00:13:23,790 --> 00:13:25,200
our family.

336
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:28,240
My husband can be a bit much sometimes,

337
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:29,360
like a big kid.

338
00:13:30,670 --> 00:13:31,200
No.

339
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:33,110
He's very nice.

340
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:34,670
You're all wonderful.

341
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:36,410
I think you're wonderful too.

342
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:38,720
The moment I saw you today, I thought,

343
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:41,000
"I wish we'd met sooner."

344
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,200
Have you...

345
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:47,700
heard about my past?

346
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:49,720
Does that matter?

347
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:59,010
I like looking at the stars.

348
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,000
Take the Andromeda Galaxy

349
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,930
we're looking at now, for example.

350
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:05,600
It's about

351
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,480
2.54 million light-years away.

352
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:10,930
It's about twice the size
of the Milky Way,

353
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:13,510
with over a trillion stars.

354
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:15,120
Yet to us,

355
00:14:15,140 --> 00:14:16,380
it's nothing more

356
00:14:16,630 --> 00:14:18,750
than a blurry patch of light.

357
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:20,840
Its vastness,

358
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:21,840
its profundity,

359
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:23,510
its brilliance,

360
00:14:23,510 --> 00:14:24,840
its true form—

361
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:26,720
most people

362
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,840
never truly

363
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:30,480
understand any of it.

364
00:14:32,630 --> 00:14:34,000
But so what?

365
00:14:34,990 --> 00:14:39,350
Humanity's limited perspective
and incomplete understanding

366
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,810
don't change

367
00:14:41,830 --> 00:14:43,230
its objective existence

368
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:45,440
or its timeless beauty.

369
00:14:48,540 --> 00:14:49,660
I understand now.

370
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,480
Actually, since my husband

371
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:56,200
likes you so much,

372
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:59,390
he must have looked into your past.

373
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:01,630
He's not as clueless as he seems.

374
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:06,000
Of course, he's not exactly smart either.

375
00:15:06,530 --> 00:15:08,010
He went bankrupt twice.

376
00:15:08,030 --> 00:15:09,910
Good thing my income is stable.

377
00:15:09,940 --> 00:15:13,000
Otherwise, our whole family
would be out on the street.

378
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:16,600
Actually...

379
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,600
ever since

380
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,480
Wang Fa's student

381
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:22,960
had that accident,

382
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:26,050
he's been carrying it with him.

383
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:29,240
We tried everything we could

384
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:30,400
to make him

385
00:15:30,510 --> 00:15:31,960
happy again.

386
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,130
But nothing really worked.

387
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,200
Today,

388
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,330
seeing him laugh...

389
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:41,850
laugh that wholeheartedly...

390
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,590
made me so, so happy.

391
00:15:49,190 --> 00:15:50,110
I think

392
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:53,920
you're the one who brought him out of it.

393
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:55,870
For your sake, he's

394
00:15:55,870 --> 00:15:57,670
finally opened his heart again.

395
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:04,200
Thank you.

396
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:22,600
Son.

397
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:24,480
Do you have to go back to Hongjing?

398
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:26,630
The guest rooms are all empty.

399
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:28,720
I can stay!

400
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:30,840
Which room will I be staying in?

401
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:32,470
Are you...

402
00:16:32,470 --> 00:16:34,000
I'm talking to my son.

403
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,000
Why are you moving around so much?

404
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:36,750
No,

405
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:38,720
Uncle, listen to me!

406
00:16:38,740 --> 00:16:44,100
I'm only 3 months and 4 days older
than Wang Tian.

407
00:16:44,510 --> 00:16:45,960
Tian, tell him

408
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:47,150
I'm only that much older than you.

409
00:16:47,150 --> 00:16:48,240
Okay. Yes, yes.

410
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,360
Quick, have the driver
take this drunk home.

411
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:51,750
No! I...

412
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:55,000
I want Fa to take me back.

413
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:57,120
-Okay, I'll take you.
-What a lightweight.

414
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:59,000
You're my former manager after all.

415
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,600
Uncle, Auntie, thank you for today.

416
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:02,600
Come by often from now on.

417
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,570
Come by often.

418
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:05,069
We're really glad you came.

419
00:17:05,069 --> 00:17:05,930
We're leaving.

420
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:07,960
Drive safely on the road.

421
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,589
We will.

422
00:17:10,310 --> 00:17:11,480
Such a lightweight.

423
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,270
So weak.

424
00:17:24,030 --> 00:17:25,560
What are you smiling about?

425
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:29,240
I just think

426
00:17:29,830 --> 00:17:31,750
your family is really lovable.

427
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:33,960
I'm so jealous.

428
00:17:38,830 --> 00:17:39,630
From now on...

429
00:17:41,510 --> 00:17:43,040
they'll be your family too.

430
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:05,810
Is this how you treat
your comrade-in-arms?

431
00:18:06,510 --> 00:18:08,440
Who said I'm his comrade-in-arms?

432
00:18:09,510 --> 00:18:10,480
Then,

433
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,200
what are we going to do with him tonight?

434
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:14,700
Let him stay at your place?

435
00:18:16,230 --> 00:18:17,070
Okay.

436
00:18:18,590 --> 00:18:19,720
That obedient?

437
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:22,110
My family tradition:

438
00:18:22,590 --> 00:18:24,920
the lady of the house makes the decisions.

439
00:19:11,840 --> 00:19:14,100
♪ Night slips through my fingers ♪

440
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:18,920
♪ Embracing the coldness of wakefulness ♪

441
00:19:19,420 --> 00:19:21,380
♪ Whispering my thoughts alone ♪

442
00:19:25,590 --> 00:19:27,240
Just kiss her if you want to.

443
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:29,350
Why are you dragging it out?

444
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:36,680
Let's go home.

445
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,440
Go home.

446
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:49,310
Do you know

447
00:19:49,310 --> 00:19:52,640
he was trying to
sneak a kiss from you just now?

448
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:57,440
Ms. Lin.

449
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,720
Tell me honestly.

450
00:20:02,270 --> 00:20:03,880
Am I really that ordinary?

451
00:20:04,550 --> 00:20:05,270
Not at all.

452
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:07,000
I think you're very special.

453
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,550
Right? Aren't I?

454
00:20:09,550 --> 00:20:11,880
Aren't I?

455
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:13,720
Let me tell you,

456
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:17,640
my handsomeness has layers.

457
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:22,030
But Tian just can't appreciate it.

458
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:23,920
I'm warning you,

459
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:26,030
if you can't keep your hands to yourself,

460
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:28,560
I'll dump you by the roadside
to feed the dogs.

461
00:20:30,070 --> 00:20:30,680
Doggie.

462
00:20:31,110 --> 00:20:31,640
Doggie.

463
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:33,200
Where's the doggie?

464
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:34,840
The doggie's over there.

465
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:37,200
The doggie's over there.

466
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:48,280
You were trying to
sneak a kiss from me just now?

467
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:54,920
If I were a doggie,

468
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:57,520
I'd want to be
a Cavalier King Charles Spaniel.

469
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:00,590
You'd better not be a dog.

470
00:21:01,790 --> 00:21:04,250
Cavalier King Charles Spaniels
are so cute.

471
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:08,010
Wrong way.

472
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:12,160
Rest early. Good night.

473
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:12,880
Good night.

474
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:14,850
Thank you for today.

475
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:15,920
Good night.

476
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,920
Thank you for everything today too.

477
00:21:21,590 --> 00:21:24,550
I could also be a Golden Retriever.

478
00:21:32,910 --> 00:21:33,560
[Wang Fa]

479
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:38,920
Hello?

480
00:21:39,690 --> 00:21:41,170
Ms. Lin,

481
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:42,790
Wang Fa lost to you!

482
00:21:42,790 --> 00:21:46,480
When are you making him
wear a flower crown?

483
00:21:47,790 --> 00:21:50,120
Can you just sleep quietly, you drunkard?

484
00:21:50,310 --> 00:21:51,160
Hello.

485
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:52,440
Don't listen to him.

486
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:53,240
Okay.

487
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:54,000
Noted.

488
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,000
Okay...

489
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,000
Okay to what?

490
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:00,460
To take you
to try on a flower crown tomorrow.

491
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:04,480
A bet's a bet, Mr. Win.

492
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:07,480
Fine.

493
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:09,310
Rest early.

494
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:10,550
You too.

495
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:23,000
Ivory,

496
00:22:23,830 --> 00:22:25,720
a bet's a bet.

497
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:29,830
What do you think of me in this outfit?

498
00:22:29,830 --> 00:22:30,790
Fix your hair.

499
00:22:30,790 --> 00:22:31,750
-It looks good.
-It really suits you.

500
00:22:31,750 --> 00:22:32,350
Excuse me.

501
00:22:32,350 --> 00:22:33,880
Come, stand a little further forward.

502
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:34,960
Look here.

503
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:39,480
Sorry.

504
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:44,880
I think I'm a bit too rough-looking

505
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,550
and too tan for the flower crown look.

506
00:22:46,550 --> 00:22:47,510
Relax.

507
00:22:47,510 --> 00:22:49,350
Places like this usually do
pretty heavy makeup.

508
00:22:49,350 --> 00:22:50,310
They'll make you nice and fair.

509
00:22:50,310 --> 00:22:51,160
Let's go.

510
00:22:52,350 --> 00:22:53,400
Okay, one more.

511
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,070
Look.

512
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:57,570
[No More Anxiety]

513
00:22:54,070 --> 00:22:55,270
Do you like this look?

514
00:22:55,960 --> 00:22:56,880
So pretty.

515
00:22:57,370 --> 00:22:58,850
So beautiful.

516
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:01,010
Here, and there's more in the back too.

517
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:04,240
I like this one as well.

518
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:04,880
Yeah.

519
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:06,240
We should take photos
in a few more outfits.

520
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,880
Okay. Do you have sample pictures?

521
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:08,790
Could you recommend a few?

522
00:23:08,790 --> 00:23:09,510
Yes, yes.

523
00:23:11,270 --> 00:23:12,330
This one's lovely.

524
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:14,310
Come on.

525
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:31,840
Does this look good on me?

526
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:32,680
Yes.

527
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,680
Let me take a picture of you.

528
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:38,650
[No More Anxiety]

529
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:43,880
Alright.

530
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:44,240
Okay.

531
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:45,030
Your turn.

532
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:49,720
Hey, you two,

533
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:50,790
would you like flower crowns?

534
00:23:50,790 --> 00:23:52,750
Ma'am, my boyfriend wants it.

535
00:23:52,750 --> 00:23:53,720
Sure.

536
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:55,960
My hair's too short
to pin anything into, right?

537
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:57,880
Even bald people can wear flower crowns.

538
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:58,880
Hear that?

539
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:00,610
Even bald people can wear them.

540
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:04,400
A bet is a bet.

541
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:05,930
I'll go pick a color for you.

542
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:08,480
Yellow, maybe.

543
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:10,020
It's more elegant.

544
00:24:15,270 --> 00:24:17,480
It was clearly a pink one in the photo,

545
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:19,030
bright pink.

546
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:21,790
It suits you perfectly.

547
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:28,000
Let me think—

548
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:30,640
we're still missing a women's qipao.

549
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:31,160
Well,

550
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:33,420
do we really have to recreate it exactly?

551
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:39,270
Ms. Lin,

552
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:40,720
please,

553
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:42,920
let me off this time.

554
00:24:44,270 --> 00:24:45,030
Alright then.

555
00:24:45,030 --> 00:24:46,920
But since we're here,

556
00:24:46,920 --> 00:24:48,720
I'll wear a flower crown myself.

557
00:24:50,310 --> 00:24:51,480
I think

558
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:52,880
it's you who wanted to wear one

559
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:54,280
from the very beginning.

560
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:56,510
That's right.

561
00:24:56,510 --> 00:24:58,200
The moment I saw your photo,

562
00:24:58,200 --> 00:24:59,860
my heart was already set on it.

563
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:03,510
Ma'am, could you pick a color for me?

564
00:25:03,510 --> 00:25:04,510
Alright.

565
00:25:04,930 --> 00:25:07,480
After you're done,
you can go take pictures by the seaside.

566
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:08,240
It'll look so pretty.

567
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:08,920
The seaside?

568
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:09,480
The seaside.

569
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:10,000
Yeah.

570
00:25:10,550 --> 00:25:12,440
The beach around here is quite beautiful.

571
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:14,170
Photos look even better there.

572
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:45,070
Look.

573
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:47,920
There's a message in a bottle over there.

574
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:49,050
What a coincidence.

575
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:58,720
It really is... quite a coincidence.

576
00:26:00,310 --> 00:26:01,510
Why don't you open it?

